Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/14435: named ellipses on right hand side of
 redex reduction signals difficult to understand error message
Date: Fri, 11 Apr 2014 07:15:54 -0500

 --047d7b33c8faade82a04f6c34b11
 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 
 Yes, it is a wording issue. You are getting the generic "I saw a bad
 underscore" error which happens to apply to ellipses here.
 
 But the suggested wording is problematic, since there isn't always an
 "RHS". For example:
 
    (term (x ..._c))
 
 is also problematic, on its own.
 
 And in a define-judgment-form "rhs" should be "output position" or similar
 thing.
 
 I could just say "this ellipsis cannot have an underscore" or something
 like that?
 
 Robby
 
 
 
 
 On Fri, Apr 11, 2014 at 5:26 AM, Matthias Felleisen <matthias@ccs.neu.edu>wrote:
 
